Colombia Stocks: Grupo Chocolates, EEB, Pacific Rubiales Advance

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-03-31T21:23:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/colombia-stocks-grupo-chocolates-eeb-pacific-rubiales-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 5 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index climbed 1.2 percent to 14,469.66, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.9 percent to 1,718.45.  Grupo Nacional de Chocolates SA (CHOCOLA)  , Colombia’s
largest food producer, jumped 1.4 percent to 23,500 pesos. The
Medellin-based company said in a filing today it plans to sell
25 million shares in the next 12 months, the equivalent of 5.4
percent of the company’s outstanding shares after the sale. It
also said it will change its name to Grupo Nutresa SA.  Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA (EEB)   rallied 3.1
percent to 177,880 pesos. EEB, as the company is known, said in
a regulatory filing yesterday its shareholders approved a 100-
for-1 stock split.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil company with fields in Colombia, climbed 4.2 percent to
51,660 pesos. The company said in a regulatory filing today it
bought a 50 percent stake in five exploration blocks in  Colombia 
from Etablissements Maurel & Prom.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
